Overview

    I have transformed cards from static objects into a reactive event-driven system. Cards now react when drawn, while
     sitting in your hand, and when played/discarded/exhausted. They can communicate with each other and have
    dynamic costs and stats.

    This enables Slay the Spire 2-style mechanics like Sly (benefits from discard), exhaust loops, and in-hand
    buffs.


    What I built in this session 

    1. Card Tags System

    Cards now have tags for synergy detection:

    this.tags = [CardTag.ATTACK, CardTag.FIRE];

    Available tags include: ATTACK, SKILL, FIRE, WATER, SLY, EXHAUST, DOT, BLOCK, HEAL, DRAW, STATUS and there may be more in the future 


    This allows cards to detect and synergize with each other. A fire buff card can now check if another card is a
    fire card and buff it.

    2. Entry Reactions

    Cards can now trigger effects when they enter your hand:

     - `onDraw(gameState)` - Called when card is drawn from deck
     - `onEnterHand(gameState, source)` - Called when card enters hand from any source (draw, generate, return from
       exhaust)

    Example use case: A card that gains 1 energy when drawn, or reduces its cost if it came from the exhaust pile.

    3. In-Hand Event Listening

    Cards can now listen for events while sitting in your hand:

      this.listenFor('cardPlayed', (data) => {
          if (data.card.tags.includes(CardTag.FIRE)) {
              this.incrementCounter('damageBuff', 1);
          }
      });

    Every time a fire card is played, this card increments its damage counter. When played later, it deals more
    damage (use wisely to stack!)

    Cards can listen for:
     - cardPlayed - When any card is played
     - cardDiscarded - When any card is discarded
     - cardExhausted - When any card is exhausted

    4. Exit Reactions

    Cards trigger effects when leaving your hand:

     - `onPlay(gameState, target)` - When card is played
     - `onDiscard(gameState)` - When card is discarded (Sly effects)
     - `onExhaust(gameState)` - When card is exhausted

    Example: A Sly card that deals 4 damage to the enemy when discarded, enabling discard-based strategies for example. 

    5. Dynamic Costs & Stats

    Card costs and stats are no longer fixed:

      getCost(gameState) {
          // Cost reduced by 1 for each water card played this turn
          const waterPlayed = gameState.counters?.waterPlayedThisTurn || 0;
          return Math.max(0, this.baseCost - waterPlayed);
      }
     
      getDamage(gameState) {
          return this.baseDamage + this.getCounter('damageBuff');
      }

    A card's cost can change based on game state, and damage can scale based on counters tracked during the turn.


    Technical Implementation

    CardPileManager now broadcasts events to all cards in hand whenever a card is played, discarded, or exhausted.
    Each card maintains its own event listener registry and counter storage.

    Memory Management: When a card leaves hand, removeAllListeners() is called to prevent memory leaks from
    accumulated callbacks.

    Impact

    This system enables complex card interactions without hardcoding synergies. Cards can now:
     - Buff each other based on tags
     - Track state across turns with counters
     - Trigger effects from any zone (hand, discard, exhaust)
     - Have costs that dynamically scale
